      "form_guide": "",
      "comment": "MISCHIEF AFOOT (8) has shown some speed at her last couple and filled minor placings, last time finishing second beaten 3.5 lengths (17.91). Yet to win here but has run some good races including four placings. The form from her last run stacks up well. Top chance in this line up. BIG RED FLIPPER (7) has hit the frame in both career runs, the latest when third (18.65) over 300m at this track. Good beginner but will need a little luck early crossing from on outside draw. Overdue to break through and rates a leading player this line up. SWIPER LANE (1) finished well back on debut when sixth (20.42) at Gunnedah over 340m. Has the inside box this time. Can do far better this time. PEPPER PUFF (2) missed the placings here on debut but looks an improver who can sneak into the finish with the right run.",
